   2         0                            ;   branches.asm -- every Type 11 Bcc
   3         0                            ;
   4         0                            ;   Adds coverage for BE, BNE, BC, BNC, BP, BN, BV, BNV, BGT, BLT,
   5         0                            ;   BH, BNH.  (BGE and BLE are already covered by bubble.asm.)
   6         0                            ;   BR and CALL (Type 25) are covered separately in call.asm because
   7         0                            ;   their addressing-mode routing is quite different.
   8         0                            ;
   9         0                            ;   Each branch targets the next label, producing a tiny chain of
  10         0                            ;   branches each 2 bytes apart.  We don't care whether each condition
  11         0                            ;   is actually taken at runtime — the test is that the assembler
  12         0                            ;   accepts every mnemonic with a bare-label (Direct) operand.
  13         0                            ;
